Japan Urged to Behave with Discretion 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries came under fire by a signed commentary of Minju Joson Saturday for talking about cooperation with south Korea in their efforts to find a solution to the "abduction issue".
 Not content with wooing the U.S. to cooperate with them in settling the "abduction issue", they are now seeking cooperation from south Korea, the commentary says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As the DPRK has clarified more than once, the Japanese reactionaries are using the "abduction issue" as a playing card in their scenario to stifle the DPRK. In other words, they try to dramatize the issue in a bid to totally blockade the DPRK under that pretext.
 They are busy calling for establishing a cooperation system with the U.S., as regards the measure for applying economic sanctions against the DPRK, and soliciting south Korea for its cooperation with them. This reveals their sinister intention to blockade the DPRK and lay a siege to it and render these actions more effective in a bid to bring down the socialist system in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Herein lie the reactionary nature of the measure taken by the Japanese reactionaries and the gravity of the issue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will employ every possible means and way to strongly react to their smear campaign to destroy its dignified socialist system.

DPRK Stand on Six-Party Talks Supported by Beninese President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Benin understands and supports the DPRK stand on the six-party talks. As a friend of the DPRK, Benin hopes that peace
would be ensured on the Korean Peninsula and Pyongyang would achieve success and wishes to see the nuclear issue settled peacefully. Beninese President Mathieu Kerekou said this when meeting with DPRK Ambassador to the country Kim Pyong Gi on Feb. 24.
 I am very pleased to learn that leader Kim Jong Il, while enjoying good health, has made tireless efforts and provided correct guidance to the work to defend the sovereignty of the country and develop economy for stabilizing the people's living, the president noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 I remember President Kim Il Sung whenever I hear news about the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is very gratifying to hear that under the correct leadership of Kim Jong Il the inter-Korean relations have made progress and the confrontation between the north and the south has been replaced by the structure of the Korean nation's confrontation with the United States since the north-south summit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. dares not invade the DPRK because Kim Jong Il has increased its defense capability, attaching great importance to military affairs despite the U.S. persistent moves to stifle it, the president stressed.

Destruction of Cold War Structure in Northeast Asia Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed commentary calls upon the countries in Northeast Asia to take joint actions against the U.S. in order to dismantle the Cold War structure in the Korean Peninsula
and the rest of the region and turn it into a nuclear-free zone.
 The commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., while giving lip-service to cooperation with China, has gone ahead, in actuality, with its strategy of containing it after regarding it as a "potential enemy."  This strategy is a grave challenge to the trend of the new century in which humankind desires peace, co-existence and prosperity, transcending the difference in ideology, political system and religion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. strategy for Northeast Asian "security" still remains a Cold War strategy aimed at containing the DPRK, China and others in reliance upon its security alliance with Japan and south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S., styling itself "the only superpower", has pursued a reactionary Asian-Pacific strategy aimed at world supremacy. That is why it is so keen to maintain the Cold War structure in Northeast Asia come what may, afraid of its collapse. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It seeks to use Japan, blinded with the ambition to realize its old dream of "Greater East Asia Co-prosperity Sphere", as a shock force for materializing its strategy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to implement the above-mentioned aggressive strategy the U.S. has deliberately strained the situation on the Korean Peninsula, raising a hue and cry over "the threat from north Korea". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. set it forth as its policy goal to bring down the political system in the DPRK, no more than a daydream, and has since hamstrung the process to improve the inter-Korean relations by hook or by crook, persistently working to isolate and stifle it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has gone the lengths of pressurizing the south Korean authorities to stop even the cooperation between the north and the south in the issue of humanitarian aid. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality goes to prove that the above-said U.S. strategy not only runs counter to the common interests of the countries in the region but is a basic factor of scuttling the six-party talks and making it impossible to realize the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should face to the reality with a cool head and dismantle the Cold War structure in Northeast Asia as early as possible.

S. Korea's Military Provocations Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- The south Korean military authorities should promptly stop their moves to strain the situation and incite confrontation in league with the United States, urges Minju Joson today in a signed commentary.
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recently the south Korean forces fired large-caliber machinegun bullets toward the north side's area near the Military Demarcation Line and introduced an artillery piece into an area close to the MDL. They also sent warships to the territorial waters of the north side in the West Sea of Korea and staged a joint anti-submarine drill in the East Sea of Korea together with the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
The U.S. is massively shipping latest war equipment into south Korea under the pretext of "reduction" and "relocation" of the U.S. forces present there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dancing to its tune, the bellicose forces of the south Korean military are actively joining the U.S. in its moves to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The military provocations going on under this situation evidently prove that the south Korean forces together with the U.S. are set to ignite a war against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is clear to everyone that such actions will chill all the fellow countrymen's daily-growing desire for national reunification and adversely affect the north-south relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military authorities' moves against the nation and reunification should not be allowed as they throw obstacles to national reconciliation and unity and the reunification of the country.

Improvement of Economic Management System Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- It would be possible to dynamically push forward the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation only when an original economic management system suitable to the developing reality and the specific conditions of the country is established and full play is given to its vitality, says Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed article.
 A steady improvement and perfection of the economic management system would provide a sure guarantee for correct guidance and management of the socialist economy, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This would also provide an important guarantee for overcoming the present difficulties and stepping up the socialist economic construction as fast as possible. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Economic guidance and management organs at all levels and officials there can fulfill high responsibility and display creativity as befitting their positions to dynamically step up the economic construction even under such difficult situation as now only when tasks, mandates and responsibilities are properly devolved upon central and local organs and enterprises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is important for improving the economic guidance and management to suit the nature of socialist society is to strictly observe the principle of attaching importance to profitability. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is necessary to steadily improve the economic management, while putting main emphasis on encouraging economic officials at all levels to conduct guidance and management assiduously in order to gain as much profits as possible in production and construction with least expenditure not only in the nationwide fields but in individual domains, regions or units. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also important for improving the economic management to strictly abide by the principle of letting the state economic organs give economic technological guidance under the political stewardship of the party. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an important socialist principle to be abided by in improving the economic management of the country to correctly combine the unified guidance of the state with the creative initiative at each unit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The economic management system in the socialist society should be improved and perfected on the principle of properly blending political and moral incentive with material one, the article stresses.

Japan's Ambition for Territorial Expansion Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Committee for the Peaceful Reunification of the Fatherland in a statement Saturday scathingly denounced the moves of the Japanese reactionaries to institute the "Day of Tok Islet" and the remarks of the Japanese ambassador to south Korea that Tok islet belongs to Japan as a very dangerous behavior fully revealing their brigandish nature and shameless ambition for territorial expansion and a heinous move to seize part of the inalienable territory of Korea.
 He said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries have become so brazenfaced as to make a claim to Tok Islet, while insisting that it belongs to Japan. This is a rash act which can be committed only by the political gangsters and rogues who are utterly indifferent to history and international law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We can never allow the Japanese reactionaries to insult the Korean nation and grab part of the inalienable land of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All Koreans should wage a more resolute struggle to shatter Japan's moves to grab the islet and force it to apologize and compensate for its past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan would be well advised to properly understand the ever mounting anti-Japanese sentiment of the Korean nation and its bitter hatred, stop acting rashly and discontinue at once its brigandish moves to grab the islet.

Spring Sowing Expected to Be Late for Abnormal Weather
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- Wheat and barley sowing would be started in late February or early March every year in Korea. This year, however, it is
expected to be some ten days late in almost rural communities because the atmosphere has remained lower than the average in March.
 Kim Mun Uk, a section chief of the Central Weather Forecast Institute of the Hydro-Meteorological Service, said that such abnormal weather is attributable to the lower temperature in winter than the average, caused by the fact that cold air has steadily come to Korea with the Siberia high atmospheric pressure and northwestern wind being further intensified than ever before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In an interview with KCNA he said such normal weather as three days cold and four warm, a result of the periodical change of high pressure and low pressure with each other, has gradually disappeared in the country in recent years so that cold continental high pressure has persisted in the country this year, too, causing cold weather. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This year's winter weather is lower than the average, more than one degree lower than last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a result, soil is frozen 30-65 cm in the most of the areas in the country, 5-10 cm more than last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the change of atmosphere expected to be serious due to the abnormal weather not only in spring but in all other seasons, it is noteworthy what effect it will give to the country's agriculture.

Agrarian Issue Solved Successfully in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- The land of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has taken on a new look suitable to the features of the powerful socialist country. Large-scale standardized fields of the country provide a glimpse of imperishable feats performed by President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il for a solution to the agrarian issue in the country.
 Right after the liberation of the country from the Japanese colonial rule, Kim Il Sung wisely directed preparations for a successful solution to an agrarian reform, considering it to be a primary task in the anti-imperialist, anti-feudal democratic revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On March 5, Juche 35 (1946) he promulgated "Law on Agrarian Reform in North Korea" and set forth the slogan "Land to the tillers!", regarding it as the basic principle to let the peasants possess land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The successful agrarian reform put an end to the feudal land ownership and the exploiting system in the country so that the peasants could free themselves from the medieval exploitation and subordination and realize their long-cherished desire for land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The President also carried out agricultural cooperativization and brought land to socialist cooperative management from individual one as required by the developing revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His far-reaching plan of land development has been creditably implemented by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He, considering it to be a long-range cause for an ultimate solution to the agrarian issue and an important undertaking for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation to completely change the appearance of land in the socialist country, started a new history of large-scale land rezoning in May 1998. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the past six years servicemen and people rezoned more than 284,800 hectares of fields in Kangwon, North Phyongan, South Hwanghae, South Phyongan and other provinces.

Foreign Ministry Spokesman Refutes U.S. Report on Human Rights
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 5 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the DPRK gave an answer to a question raised by KCNA Saturday in which it accused the United States of groundlessly pulling up the DPRK over the "human rights issue".
 He says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. State Department in an annual report on human rights on Feb. 28 again said this or that about human rights performances in more than 100 countries including the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. ballyhoo about human rights practices every year does not deserve even a passing note. This can be made only by the Bush group, a mastermind of swindling and deception. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK does neither pay heed to it nor listen to it. It is nothing surprising for the Bush administration to utter such words as it has inveterate enmity toward the system in the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is, therefore, not interested at all in dealing with Washington.

Japan Urged to Shake off Its Ill-Fame as War Criminal State
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- Japan should properly opt to honestly liquidate its past as Germany did, says Rodong Sinmun Sunday in a signed article.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan still refuses to reflect on the unspeakable pain and misfortune it imposed upon the Korean people and liquidate the past. This is quite contrary to the honest attitude taken by Germany to redress its past crimes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
This wrongdoing of Japan is little short of rubbing salt into the wounds of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan has not yet made any honest apology and repentance of the crimes of aggression it committed in the past 60 years after its defeat in the Pacific War. Worse still, it has no idea of compensation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The liquidation of the past is a historic commitment of Japan and a demand of the times. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The crimes Japan committed against the Korean and the Asian people in the past can never be concealed. It should pay for these crimes without fail any time. If the Japanese militarists try to keep them buried into oblivion with the passage of time, far from making an honest apology and repentance of them, this will add to the crimes perpetrated by Japan and it will not escape a judgment by history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The world peace-loving people want Japan to make a proper settlement of its past crimes and make a clean sheet. Japan's apology and compensation for its past crimes would be a yardstick showing whether it wants to improve relations with its neighboring countries and take the road of peace or not. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese ruling quarters should admit their wrong approach towards their past history and take a correct road. If they do so, there will be a way out for them and if not, they will meet a disaster.

March First Popular Uprising Marked in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- Functions were held across south Korea to mark the 86th anniversary of the March First Popular Uprising, according to south Korean MBC.
 A function for commemorating the day took place in front of Kwanghwamun, Seoul, on March 2 with at least 10,000 members of civic, social and religious organizations attending and a similar function took place in Chonan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At least 200 residents in Ullung County held a ceremony marking the day on Tok Islet and a meeting condemning Japan's ambition to seize the islet and vowing to wage a strong campaign to protect the islet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, similar functions took place in Kyonggi Province, Pusan and other places.

Women's Meeting Held in South Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- The Women's Committee of the Reunification Solidarity and the Council for the Solution of the Issue of the Volunteers
Corps in south Korea reportedly held a meeting demanding a solution to the issue of "comfort women" for the imperial Japanese army in front of the Japanese embassy in Seoul Wednesday in the run-up to the World Women's Day (March 8).
 Present there were members of civic and social organizations and surviving "comfort women." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers at the meeting called for keeping watchful eyes on Japan which has not yet made any apology and compensation for its crimes but dreamt of reviving militarism in a bid to realize its wild ambition for aggression. It is the way of protecting the national sovereignty and advancing history to eliminate the remnants of the Japanese imperialists, they added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution was adopted at the meeting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the government authorities to settle the issue of "comfort women" this year without fail and opt for properly settling the past.

Anti-National Decision of S. Korean Supreme Court Flayed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, March 6 (KCNA) -- The supreme court of south Korea recently took such a fascist action as making an unjust decision against Kim Chong Il,
chairman of the All-People Committee for Measures against the Murder of the Two Schoolgirls by an Armoured Car of the U.S. Forces, on the charge of leading "illegal" mass candlelight rallies of south Koreans staged in protest against the incident that occurred in 2002.
 A spokesman for the Secretariat of the Central Committee of the Democratic Front for the Reunification of the Fatherland issued a statement on Saturday in this regard, which said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This ruling is an intolerable insult to millions of south Koreans from all walks of life who participated in the rallies and to all other Koreans who fully supported them. It is little short of the thrice-cursed double killing of  Sim Mi Son and Sin Hyo Sun, the schoolgirls murdered by the U.S. imperialist aggressor troops in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement bitterly denounced this action taken by the south Korean judicial authorities as an intolerable infringement upon the dignity and sovereignty of the Korean nation and an unpardonable anti-national criminal act of blatantly challenging the desire of the south Koreans to live in a new independent world free from foreign forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The situation prevailing in south Korea today clearly proves that those pro-U.S. sycophantic treacherous forces are a stumbling block lying in the way of achieving independence and democracy in the south Korean society and that the desire of the south Koreans for a new independent policy and life can never come true as long as such traitors to the nation are left unpunished, the statement said, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The south Korean judicial authorities should face up to the trend of the times, revoke at once their unfair judgment made as regards the rallies and immediately withdraw the sentences passed on those who participated in the just struggle.
